This is a simple project to demonstrate some ideas behind few technologies.
First of all, this is Electron application (right now it's configured and tested strictly on Mac OS X 10.9.x),
which is using babel for compiling JavaScript ES6 to more compatible version of JS, ES5.
Moreover Webpack is used to do the babel compilation and to compact all scripts to fever files that can be loaded by index.html in less requests.
Webpack can be also called with 'PROD=true' variable to do Dedupe (remove duplicates), Uglify and Minifi the JS code.